Currently I have a situation where I am using a JIRA Issue macro to show a list of JIRA issues.  Some of these issues are actually linked back to pages on my Confluence instance.  When I specify to show Linked Issues in my JIRA Issue macro list, the column does not include linked Confluence pages.  Perhaps this column is not the best spot for such information, perhaps a separate column called Linked Pages or Linked Sites would be preferable, but I would absolutely love the ability to show linked pages for each of the JIRA issues in my list using the inbuilt macro.  

Any other workarounds for this situation would be gladly appreciated.
